Sisa Canca, News24Taxis. (Duncan Alfreds, News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man was shot dead while another was&nbsp;critically wounded in a shootout at the Makhetha Shopping Centre in&nbsp;Soweto on Friday morning.&nbsp;Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela said an unidentified number of people in a white sedan shot at a parked minibus taxi outside the shopping complex and drove off. The survivor is said to be in critical condition. Makhubela said a case of murder and attempted murder has been opened.&nbsp; Arrests are yet to be made.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.